CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 9, 1941, pg. 3 reads: "James Weldon Johnson Camp Model Project - Above are scenes from Camp James Weldon Johnson, situated on Raccoon Creek in foothills of the beautiful Allegehney [Allegheny] mountains just 34 miles from Pittsburg. Some of the children who enjoyed the facilities of the spacious grounds during the past two weeks are pictured...Bottom: Nurse Eunice Cook administers to a camper who complained of a sore throat, while a girl camper stands by for a weight check-up.  Mrs. Cook is from Pittsburgh."
TitMainTitle: Eunice Cook looking in boy's throat, with another woman standing beside table with medicine, at Camp Weldon Johnson, Beaver County, Pennsylvania
